<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Shared-Memory on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/shared-memory/</link><description>Recent content in Shared-Memory on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/shared-memory/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>[Solution] C errno EIDRM — Identifier removed Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/errno-eidrm/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/errno-eidrm/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="solution-c-errno-eidrm--identifier-removed-fix"&gt;[Solution] C errno EIDRM — Identifier removed Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;When a process attempts to access an IPC resource (message queue, semaphore set, or shared memory segment) that has been removed by another process, the system call fails and sets &lt;code&gt;errno&lt;/code&gt; to &lt;code&gt;EIDRM&lt;/code&gt;. This is a race condition in multi-process applications.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Another process called &lt;code&gt;msgctl(IPC_RMID)&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;semctl(IPC_RMID)&lt;/code&gt;, or &lt;code&gt;shmctl(IPC_RMID)&lt;/code&gt; to remove the IPC resource.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A race condition where one process removes the IPC resource while another is still using it.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The IPC resource was removed during a blocking operation (e.g., &lt;code&gt;msgrcv()&lt;/code&gt; waiting).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Process cleanup code removes IPC resources prematurely.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Check for the existence of IPC resources before accessing them. Use signal handlers or cleanup routines carefully.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] ORA-04031: Unable to Allocate Shared Memory</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tools/oracle/ora-04031/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tools/oracle/ora-04031/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="ora-04031-unable-to-allocate-shared-memory"&gt;ORA-04031: Unable to Allocate Shared Memory&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;ORA-04031 occurs when Oracle cannot allocate a contiguous block of shared memory from the shared pool. The SGA is fragmented or too small for the current workload.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The shared pool is too small for the application&amp;rsquo;s cursor usage&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excessive hard parsing due to lack of bind variables&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Shared pool fragmentation from many small allocations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Large PL/SQL packages or cursor caching consuming shared memory&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="check-shared-pool-size"&gt;Check Shared Pool Size&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-sql" data-lang="sql"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;SELECT&lt;/span&gt; name, value &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;/&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1024&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;/&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1024&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;AS&lt;/span&gt; mb
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;FROM&lt;/span&gt; v$sga
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;WHERE&lt;/span&gt; name &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;IN&lt;/span&gt; (&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;Shared Pool&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;Large Pool&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;Java Pool&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="increase-shared-pool-size"&gt;Increase Shared Pool Size&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-sql" data-lang="sql"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;ALTER&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;SYSTEM&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;SET&lt;/span&gt; shared_pool_size &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;4&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;G&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;SCOPE&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;BOTH&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="flush-shared-pool"&gt;Flush Shared Pool&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-sql" data-lang="sql"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- Temporary fix: flush shared pool
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;ALTER&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;SYSTEM&lt;/span&gt; FLUSH SHARED_POOL;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="use-bind-variables-to-reduce-parsing"&gt;Use Bind Variables to Reduce Parsing&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-sql" data-lang="sql"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- WRONG: hard parse every time
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;EXECUTE&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;IMMEDIATE&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;SELECT * FROM users WHERE id = &amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;||&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;123&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- CORRECT: bind variables reduce shared pool usage
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;EXECUTE&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;IMMEDIATE&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;SELECT * FROM users WHERE id = :1&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;USING&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;123&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="enable-automatic-memory-management"&gt;Enable Automatic Memory Management&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-sql" data-lang="sql"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;ALTER&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;SYSTEM&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;SET&lt;/span&gt; sga_target &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;16&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;G&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;SCOPE&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;BOTH&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;ALTER&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;SYSTEM&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;SET&lt;/span&gt; sga_max_size &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;16&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;G&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;SCOPE&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;SPFILE;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="examples"&gt;Examples&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-sql" data-lang="sql"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- Cursor exhaustion
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;BEGIN&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;FOR&lt;/span&gt; i &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;IN&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;..&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;100000&lt;/span&gt; LOOP
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;EXECUTE&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;IMMEDIATE&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;SELECT count(*) FROM tab&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;||&lt;/span&gt; i;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;END&lt;/span&gt; LOOP;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;END&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- ORA-04031: unable to allocate 4192 bytes of shared memory
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- Fix: use bind variables and increase shared_pool_size
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tools/oracle/ora-00600/"&gt;ORA-00600&lt;/a&gt; — internal error&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tools/oracle/ora-01652/"&gt;ORA-01652&lt;/a&gt; — temp segment extension failure&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>